node.text:
The past year and a half tested us all in ways we weren’t expecting, and our community rose to meet the challenges by getting tested and following guidelines designed to keep us all safe and healthy. 

Now vaccines are widely available, Covid-19 case counts have remained low on campus, and we’re ready to move forward. Here’s what you need to know about #JacketsMovingForward. 🐝

node.text:
Connecting via Skype, Georgia Tech talked with Astronaut and Georgia Tech graduate Shane Kimbrough and his Japanese colleague Aki Hoshide at the International Space Station. 

During the inflight interview, Kimbrough and Hoshide talked about the energy around space exploration, the role of commanding the ISS, and plans to capture some pretty interesting images from the windows of the station.

node.title: GT Talks to Shane Kimbrough & Aki Hoshide at the Int'l Space Station

node.text:
Georgia Tech aerospace engineering student Anthony Limiero, built his own custom unicycle on campus and then rode it more than 300 miles from his parents' home in Tennessee back to  Atlanta. 

As president of Georgia Tech's unicycling club Limiero has also taught dozens of his classmates how to ride a unicycle.

node.title: Georgia Tech Student Builds Unicycle and Rides It 300 Miles Back To Campus

node.text: Advising seven U.S. presidents and leading research efforts in emerging diseases like Covid-19, Dr. Anthony Fauci has served on the front line of disease outbreaks for decades. Yesterday afternoon, Fauci was bestowed the Ivan Allen Jr. Prize for Social Courage in a hybrid virtual ceremony on Georgia Tech's campus.

node.title: Dr. Anthony Fauci receives the Ivan Allen Jr. Prize for Social Courage

node.text:
“Covid-19 may have changed the way we do some things, but it also highlighted our strength and resilience. Now that same commitment and resolve is how we must move forward. It’s vital that we critically reflect not only on our rights to individual autonomy and free choice, but also on our responsibility to others. It is very important that we all follow current recommendations.” 

Read the full message from President Ángel Cabrera by swiping up the link in our story above. #JacketsMovingForward
